args: Renee found a lot to admire with her elder sisters\nin terms of how they behaved inside the smithy.\nOnce they left it, however...
No! Get up! Ugh! Why do we have to\ndo this every day?!
Hee hee! Sounds like someone could\nuse a cup of tea to help them get up.
Great idea, Rena. Lemme just... Um...
PFFFFFT! Bleeeeech! I knew it!\nYou mixed up the sugar with salt!
Then why are you holding a saltshaker?
I didn't mix them up—I did it on purpose!\nI thought the salt would help her get up.
Oh! Well, if that's what you did, then...
Wait, that's a TERRIBLE idea! Ugh!\nWhy are you always like this?!
Ramonaaaaa! Get up right now before\nI throw this salty tea in your dumb face!
Alas, once outside the smithy, it was Renee\nwho had to look after her elder sisters.
Urrrrgh. Ramona is SUCH a slob\nonce she knocks off work!
And Rena is...well Rena's Rena even when\nshe's at work...
I have to work ten times as hard\njust to make up for them.
If they were both more dependable,\nI could go out and have a BOATLOAD\nof new experiences!
Ah, there is nothing better than starting\na day as the sun peeks over the horizon.

A loss of discipline in one's daily life
will surely appear in one's work.
That is why an artisan must always
be early to bed and early to rise.
Hee hee! You always have been\nsuper disciplined like that, Ramona.
Good morning, my dear sisters.\nI have prepared breakfast.
We have fresh sausage from the market\nand scrambled eggs laid only yesterday.
Ahhh... I'm so lucky to have two\nperfect sisters...
Oh man, that would be the BEST.
I'd totally be able to leave everything\nto Rena and Ramona.
I have finished all of the cleaning!
And I have completed the washing!
But of course! I give any work my all,\nwhether in the smithy or the home.
We do not need you to do anything at all.
That's right. Leave everything to us!
Yaaay! Then I'm gonna head out\nand experience stuff!
Do have a safe trip, my dearest sister!\nNow then, Rena, for our next weapon,\nwe will need...
Ah, yes. I wondered about that...
Uh, guys? I'm happy to help with\nWORK work if that's what you—
Please, do not trouble yourself!\nRena and I can handle it.
Do you not remember what I said earlier?
We do not need you to do anything.
Now then, getting back to our discussion...
Of course. What do you think of this idea?
I didn't like that at ALL.
I thought it would be amazing at first,\nbut if they ever got their acts together,\nthey totally wouldn't need me!
I have seen a possible future,\nand it is terrifying...
Hee hee! You're not supposed to fall\nasleep while you're eating, Ramona.
Blaaaah... Mine still has peppers\nand carrots in it.
Oh, I'm sorry! I forgot!\nLet me just pick those out...
Say, aren't you going to get angry\nwith us today like you usually do?
Of course not, silly! I love you both\njuuuust the way you are!
Ahhh... I'm so lucky to have two\nhopeless sisters...
